column5: After my son was sick for almost 3 weeks, I needed to give him a great day of shore fishing on Sunday.  We both got new pb crappie and a new catfish record too. 16 slabs (12 home), 5 oos bas, 1 pike (him) and catfish plus a few nice sized rockies. A turtle got a hold of our stringer before we left, leaving 2 crappie heads for us to laugh at. His crappie was 12" and mine was 14".  You can see assumed claw marks on the 14 from the snapper. Lucky I got a pic at all!!
Wow, nice bunch of fish there!
That is one happy young fella
Nice dinner plate sizes, looks like you guys had fun
Good haul. Nothing like an outing with the kids.
